<div id="review_60190909" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/60190909" />
    <a title="Devani" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2430822-devani"><img alt="Devani" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/60190909?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Devani" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Devani" href="/user/show/2430822-devani">Devani</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2430822-devani?shelf=buy-it">buy-it</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer60190909" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6952982050424290979">I really dug this book in a big way...I think I need to buy my own copy of it. At first it sounded like just another volume of new-agey pap, but Oriah Mountain Dreamer actually had a lot of very intelligent things to say, and called shit where she saw it (which I always respect). She offers very grounded permission for the reader to accept herself, and it turned out to be a comforting read. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

